    • Constructor Detail

      • LocateStatus

        public LocateStatus(long id,
            java.util.Date date,
            java.lang.String location,
            java.lang.String timeZone,
            twitter4j.Status status,
            boolean tweet,
            boolean accountLocated,
            boolean retweetLocated)
        creates a new storage-object to add an account/retweet to the database
        Parameters:
        id - the twitter-id of the account where the tweet was from as long
        date - the date of the retweet as Date
        location - the location of the account, wherefrom the retweet was as String
        timeZone - the timeZone of the user who created the retweet as String
        status - the status that contains the user/account to add
        tweet - false if this account was extracted from a retweet-status-object, else true
        accountLocated - true if the account has been located and wrote into the database, else false
        retweetLocated - true if the retweet has been located and the location-code is in the parameter location, else false
